cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with segmentation of biomedical images using deep learning. The use of convolutional neural networks and objective functions also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The discussion about the best objective function for sparse data also suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of magnetic resonance angiography images suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
